Package org.moeaframework.analysis.sensitivity

Class ExtractData

java.lang.Object
org.moeaframework.util.CommandLineUtility
org.moeaframework.analysis.sensitivity.ExtractData
public class ExtractData extends CommandLineUtility
Command line utility for extracting data from a result file. The data that can be extracted includes any properties by providing its full name, or any of the following metrics if given the designated +option. The available options include:
  • +hypervolume for Hypervolume
  • +generational for GenerationalDistance
  • +inverted for InvertedGenerationalDistance
  • +epsilon for AdditiveEpsilonIndicator
  • +error for MaximumParetoFrontError
  • +spacing for Spacing
  • +contribution for Contribution
  • +R1 for R1Indicator
  • +R2 for R2Indicator
  • +R3 for R3Indicator

Usage: java -cp "..." org.moeaframework.analysis.sensitivity.ExtractData <options> <fields>

Arguments:

-b, --problem The name of the problem. This name should reference one of the problems recognized by the MOEA Framework.
-d, --dimension The number of objectives (use instead of -b).
-i, --input The result file containing the input data.
-o, --output The output file where the extract data will be saved.
-s, --separator The character used to separate entries in the output file.
-e, --epsilon The epsilon values for limiting the size of the results. This epsilon value is also used for any algorithms that include an epsilon parameter.
-r, --reference Location of the reference file used when computing the performance metrics (required if -m is set).
-n, --noheader Do not include a header line indicating the data stored in each column.
<fields> The names of the fields to extract from the data, or one of the +options listed above.
